title: For Sale:  SOLD (Used) LaRue Tactical Model LT-15 16.1 Inch PredatOBR 5.56
postcontent: GREAT DEALS SELL QUICKLY, CHECK HERE FOR AVAILABILITY OR TO PURCHASE> (Used) LaRue Tactical Model LT-15 16.1 Inch PredatOBR 5.56(Used) LaRue Tactical Model LT-15 16.1 Inch PredatOBR 5.56DOES NOT COME WITH THE CORRECT CASE The PredatOBR 5.56 was designed for those who are searching for a hybrid cross between the standard OBR and PredatAR 5.56x45 Rifles. The most remarkable feature of the PredatOBR is its ability to be completely “broken down” and stored into the optional Rollup Bag and Toolbox. The PredatOBR handguard has a locking stainless steel QD Lever system on each side. Once the levers are released, the handguard slides off of the upper assembly in seconds. The PredatOBR's barrel can easily be removed with the supplied PredatOBR Barrel Wrench, unscrew the Barrel Nut from Receiver and pull the Barrel Assembly free from Receiver. No need to remove the gas tube, gas block or muzzle device. Reverse the process to reinstall. Hand-tighten Barrel Nut and torque approximately 1/8-turn past hand-tight (Approximately 40-50 foot pounds). Once reassembled correctly, the point of impact (POI) shift will be 0.0 to 0.5 MOA of the original.PredatOBR barrels are chambered in 5.56x45mm, and feature rifling in a 1/8 twist rate. All muzzles are threaded in 1/2 x 28. Like the OBR and PredatAR riles, LaRue has eliminated the conventional AR barrel nut and bolt the handguard directly to the proprietary upper receiver, creating a true “free-float” barrel. The handguard does not touch the barrel or barrel nut at any place. The zero-MOA upper rail provides plenty of room for weapon-mounted night-vision day/night combinations. Both the upper and lower are CNC-machined from billet aluminum for the optimum fit and consistency. Even though it has been lightened certain features, there is still additional material in strategic areas to achieve maximum accuracy.The PredatOBR has threaded stainless-steel hard-points over the entire length of the handguard at the 3, 6, and 9 o’clock positions. These hard-points have an integral spine built-in for structural support. Provided with the system are three 3-inch MIL-STD-1913 rail sections that can be positioned anywhere along the handguard, per operator preference. These rail sections are attachable/detachable using a supplied tool (Torx® T-15 wrench). The rail sections are CNC-machined from billet aluminum. This robust solution provides a perfect precision mounting space for aiming lasers, illumination and bipods.The PredatOBR's Port Selector Technology™ (PST) gas block is adjustable, to aid in the optimum function when using a sound suppressor. This special gas block contains a dual port mechanism that is operated by rotating a lever from one side to another. When the lever is rotated to the right-side of the rifle, the gasses are reduced, to compensate for the extra blowback created by the suppressor. When rotated to the left side, the gasses are increased for use without a suppressor.The LaRue Tactical 6-position Retract Action Trigger (R.A.T.) Stock comes standard with every PredatOBR. It is ergonomic, has protected control surfaces and contains a set of cleaning rods in an internal compartment. Since the height of the 12 o’clock rail is at the optimum position, there is no need for a cheek riser as part of this system. The New A-PEG grip also comes standard. This grip was designed to be ambidextrous and places the hand in the corrected position for precision shooting.Specifications:Caliber: 5.56 x 45 mm NATOBarrel Lengths: 14.5”,16.1”,18",and 20"Rifling Twist Rate: 1/8Barrel Life: 10,000 (approx)Gas System: Direct Impingement with LaRue PST™ port selectorTrigger: LaRue MBTAbout LaRue Firearm Accuracy:LaRue accuracy is known world-wide. The accuracy of each LaRue Rifle is proven at our 100-yard tunnel using match-grade ammunition. No LaRue firearm can leave the facility unless it obtains accuracy of less-than 1 MOA (1.047”) at 100 Yards. Each firearm ships with a copy of a 3-round group obtained from that actual firearm. While we guarantee the rifle is capable of sub-MOA accuracy, we can not guarantee the end-user will be able to shoot sub-MOA…since we have no control over shooting proficiency, familiarity with the system, ammunition choice, environmental factors, etc. LaRue firearms are precision instruments that require discipline, training, proper ammunition and maintenance to yield the best results.PredatOBR is a registered trademark.

The muzzle brake is a clamp on not a screw on and can easily be removed if desired.

title: For Sale/Trade:  16" mid-length 223 wylde AR-15, FDE furniture
postcontent:
This is for the complete AR-15 rifle pictured.

This rifle has a PSA mil-spec upper, lower, and bolt carrier group.  Upper receiver has been accurized by having the surface that mates with the barrel extension trued.  Action has been tuned using a high speed camera to select buffer weight and action spring.  No bolt bounce at all.  Action runs like corn through a goose.

Here's some bullet points on the barrel:
• 16" barrel with heavy tapered profile (34 oz barrel)
• chambered in 223 wylde (5.56 NATO or 223 remington)
• mid-length gas port
• 1:8 twist 5R rifling
• 1/2x28 pitch threaded barrel
• .085" gas port
• 4150 CMV steel construction
• 4140 CMV steel extension w/ polished M4 feed ramps
• QPQ finish inside and out

For those unfamiliar QPQ finish adds longer barrel life than chrome-lining, is more corrosion resistant, and since it is a salt-bath treatment rather than a lining it doesn't degrade accuracy by affecting the dimensions like chrome lining does.

Furniture consists of a Magpul CTR buttstock, Strike Industries pistol grip (the one that looks like a 'murican flag), and Custom carbon fiber free floating hand guard all finished in FDE.

The stock features a limbsaver buttpad which gives the stock just enough length to keep the sumbitch from pulling out facial hair.  It also takes a gun that barely had any recoil to begin with and makes it a child soldier's dream.

The carbon fiber handguard was cerakoted by Controlled Chaos Arms in magpul FDE and is built using AP Customs hardware.  Cerakote is both to improve the look but also to protect the carbon fiber from any cleaners that might damage the resin.  Needless to say this handguard is extremely light.  It also has the advantage of using a normal mil spec barrel nut and features an AP customs QD sling socket on the left side.  Very cool one-of-a-kind handguard.

Other parts include YHM front sight block, Magpul rear MBUS sight in FDE, polished Milspec fire control group.  Muzzle device is a beat up cavcomp taken off an older rifle but it keeps her shooting flat.  All other parts have fired just 80 rounds to tune the action and ensure reliability.  This is a thoughtfully assembled rifle intended to meet or exceed the accuracy and reliability required for any role an AR-15 might be used in.  Rifle was originally intended for a good friend but he's moving someplace where awesome guns aren't welcome.  His disarmament is your gain.

title: For Sale/Trade:  CUSTOM SPIKES AR PISTOL. AN ULTIMATE TRUCK GUN.
postcontent:
Did you know that this AR15 pistol is headshot-accurate up to 200+ yards?

Did you know that you can have this weapon fully loaded with a 100 round drum magazine, resting on the passenger seat of your car LEGALLY?

Are you familiar with the difference in lethality between a rifle cartridge and a pistol cartridge?

If not, let me start by saying that only about 1 in 13 people actually DIE when shot with a pistol caliber weapon. And that death, if you're lucky enough for it to happen, is most commonly the result of a long term "bleed-out" rather than the result of the instantaneous death associated with the concussive trauma that a rifle cartridge causes.

The reason for this is that pistol cartridges don't offer the sufficient velocity to kill a threat reliably. Weapon platforms that utilize pistol cartridges are known as "secondary weapons" by the military -- but are more commonly known as "side arms" by the general public. 

The reason that guns which support pistol cartridges are known as "secondary weapons" is due to the fact that they were never intended as a primary means of killing a threat. They were invented, solely and only, as a means to (when a solider is separated from his/her primary weapon) fight your way BACK to your primary weapon platform. THAT is the main reason why secondary weapons exist at all.

So when you consider the size, the weight, and the classification of an AR Pistol, you are dealing with a weapon system that is by FAR more accurate and deadly than ANY other "pistol caliber" platform can EVER hope to provide. 

It is for that reason that you should consider this high-level, customized, and barely used AR15 Pistol platform. This is unequivocally the most deadly weapon on earth that you as an american can carry on your person or fully-loaded, chambered, and in your car due to it's classification as a pistol and not a rifle. 

However, I hope you realized that this gun, while classified as a pistol, accurately fires a rifle caliber projectile which, due to it's velocity, offers up FAR greater lethality than ANY pistol on the market (revolver or otherwise) can hope to match.

Send a PM for all of the custom parts included in this package. 

Asking $1200
